mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.directory
Class ConsumerViewInterpreter

java.lang.Object
  mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.FieldListener
      mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.ViewInterpreter
          mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.directory.ConsumerViewInterpreter
public class ConsumerViewInterpreter
extends ViewInterpreter

This view interpreter listens to the DIRECTORY field of the AuthoritativeState. It projects the ADDED and REMOVED fields.

Inputs from State:

  • DirectoryFields.DIRECTORY_FIELDNAME is a Map with ServerContact as keys and String as values. The String is a human-readable description of the information offered by advertiser.

Outputs to clients:

  • DirectoryFields.ADDED is a Map:ServerContact-->String as described above.
  • DirectoryFields.REMOVED is a Map:ServerContact-->String as described above.

Constructor Detail

ConsumerViewInterpreter

public ConsumerViewInterpreter(State s)
Class constructor that uses a State. This ConsumerViewInterpreter watches the Field DirectoryFields.DIRECTORY_FIELDNAME in s. It outputs two fields: DirectoryFields.ADDED and DirectoryFields.REMOVED.

It complains if DIRECTORY_FIELDNAME is not a member of s.

BUG: Does not throw an exception (such as NoSuchFieldException) if s has no Field named DirectoryFields.DIRECTORY_FIELDNAME. Throwing an Exception has consequences for the Projector and for the other ViewInterpreter classes.
